SAFMA was registered as a society in August 1999 in New Delhi with both lawyers and social workers as its founding members. The members came together with the shared objective of providing legal aid and assistance to the vulnerable & marginalized sections of society so as to use law in the process of social development and reform. The members and associates of SAFMA have been continuously involved with efforts combining socio-economic strategies with human rights based focus. SAFMA has been working in the field of demystifying the law and making it more accessible so that people can use the law to assert their rights.
